textAfterTable: High School: Dixon was a three-sport star at Lugoff-Elgin High School, lettering in basketball, tennis and track and field. She was an All-Region selection, was a four-time basketball MVP and was also a four-time team captain. She was a member of the National Honor Society, Beta Club, Future Educators of America, National Society of High School Scholars and the Upstate Junior Scholars.
